scott lyons <slyons(-at-)germansupply.com> wrote:
On 3/18/05 10:53 AM, "Richard Atwell" wrote:

> This Boston Bob advice has been mentioned many times in the archives:
> 
> http://www.bostonengine.com/articles/hbmanifold.htm


It's good, but he doesn't mention heating the copper ring to red hot (then
let cool) before installing. This helps a lot, it anneals the copper, making
it deform better to the flanges. A small smear of Loctite 518 also helps get
a perfect seal, as well as holding the ring in place during assembly.


